# ⚙️ External Integrations Setup Guide

This guide will walk you through setting up the automated systems for your CRM. Follow these steps to enable Google Calendar synchronization, automated emails, and WhatsApp messaging.

---

## 1. Google Calendar & Meet Setup
The CRM uses a "Google Service Account" to create calendar events and Google Meet links automatically.

### Step A: Create a Google Cloud Project
1. Go to the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/).
2. Create a **New Project** (e.g., "GT Group CRM").
3. Search for **"Google Calendar API"** in the search bar and click **Enable**.

### Step B: Create a Service Account
1. Go to **IAM & Admin > Service Accounts**.
2. Click **+ Create Service Account**.
3. Name it "CRM-Sync" and click **Create and Continue**.
4. Skip the optional roles and click **Done**.

### Step C: Generate the JSON Key
1. Click on the newly created service account email.
2. Go to the **Keys** tab.
3. Click **Add Key > Create New Key**.
4. Select **JSON** and click **Create**. A file will download to your computer.
5. **Paste the contents of this JSON file** into the "Google Service Account JSON" box in the CRM.

### Step D: Share your Calendar
1. Copy the service account email (it looks like `crm-sync@project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com`).
2. Open your [Google Calendar](https://calendar.google.com/) (using your `social.gtbd@gmail.com` account).
3. Go to **Settings > Settings for my calendars > [Your Email] > Share with specific people**.
4. Click **Add people** and paste the Service Account email.
5. Set permission to **"Make changes to events"**.

---

## 2. Messaging & Alerts (Email)
We use [Resend](https://resend.com) for professional, high-deliverability emails.

1. Create a free account at [Resend.com](https://resend.com).
2. Go to **API Keys** and click **Create API Key**.
3. Set the name to "CRM Production" and the permission to "Full Access".
4. Copy the key (starts with `re_...`) and paste it into the **Resend API Key** box in the CRM.
5. *(Optional/Recommended)* Go to **Domains** in Resend and add `gt-bd.com` (or your preferred domain) to remove the "via resend.com" label.

---

## 3. WhatsApp Business (Optional)
By default, the CRM uses a free "Click-to-Send" method. For automated bots:

1. Create a Meta App at [developers.facebook.com](https://developers.facebook.com).
2. Add the **WhatsApp** product.
3. Under **WhatsApp > Getting Started**, you will find your **Temporary Access Token** and **Phone Number ID**.
4. Paste them in the format `PhoneID / Token` in the CRM.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Always click **"Save Changes"** at the top right after pasting your credentials. If a key is invalid, the CRM will alert you when it tries to send a notification.
